# Pythia workspace guardrails
# These rules are installed to .codex/rules/default.rules by pythia init/update.

- Do not use shell redirection (> or >>) to write into .pythia/workflows/, .pythia/config/settings.md, .pythia/config/paths.md, .pythia/README.md, or generated cache dirs (.claude/skills, .agents/skills, .cursor/skills).
  Use structured edit tools (Edit/Write/apply_patch) instead.

- Generated cache dirs (.claude/skills, .agents/skills, .cursor/skills) are regenerated on every `pythia update`.
  Edit the source in skills/ — your changes to the generated copies will be overwritten.

- Workflow documents (*.plan.md, *.review.md, *.implementation.md, *.audit.md) are role-owned.
  Only the responsible skill (/plan, /review, /implement, /audit) should write these files directly.
